'''核糖体DNA'''（Ribosomal DNA，rDNA）是一种[[DNA|DNA]][[DNA序列|序列]]，该序列用于[[核糖体RNA|rRNA]]编码。核糖体是[[蛋白质|蛋白质]]和rRNA分子的组合，[[翻译_(遗传学)|翻译]][[mRNA|mRNA]]分子以产生蛋白质的组件。如该图所示，[[真核生物|真核生物]]的rDNA包括一个单元段，一个[[操纵子|操纵子]]，以及由{{le|非转录间隔区|Non-transcribed spacer|NTS}}、{{le|ETS转录因子家族|ETS transcription factor family|ETS}}、{{le|18S|18S ribosomal RNA}}、{{le|ITS1|ITS1}}、{{le|5.8S|5.8S ribosomal RNA}}、{{le|ITS2|ITS2}}和{{le|28S|28S ribosomal RNA}}束组成的[[串联重复序列|串联重复序列]]。rDNA的还有另一个基因，由[[5S_核糖体RNA|5S]] rRNA基因编码，位于大多数真核生物的基因组中<ref name=Richard>{{cite journal|title=Comparative Genomics and Molecular Dynamics of DNA Repeats in Eukaryotes|date=2008-12-01|doi=10.1128/mmbr.00011-08|language=en|journal=Microbiology and Molecular Biology Reviews|volume=72|issue=4|url=http://mmbr.asm.org/content/72/4/686|pages=686–727|issn=1092-2172|accessdate=2018-04-03|author=Guy-Franck Richard, Alix Kerrest, Bernard Dujon|archive-date=2021-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210315143658/https://mmbr.asm.org/content/72/4/686|dead-url=no}}</ref>。5S rDNA序列也存在于[[果蝇|果蝇]]的串联重复序列<ref name=Richard/>。

== 重复单元的序列同质性 ==
在大型的rDNA序列，rDNA的{{le|重复单元|Repeat unit}}之间的多态性非常低，这表明rDNA的串联阵列通过[[协同进化|协同进化]]演变<ref name=Richard/>。在对9种果蝇的5S串联重复序列区域彼此进行比较后得出的结果表明，因这一区域[[插入_(遺傳學)|插入]]和[[刪除_(遺傳學)|删除]]较为频繁，在[[5'端|5'端]]以及[[3'端|3'端]]两侧发现有[[保守序列|保守序列]]<ref name=Paques>{{cite journal |last1=Päques |first1=F |last2=Samson |first2=ML |last3=Jordan |first3=P |last4=Wegnez |first4=M |title=Structural evolution of the Drosophila 5S ribosomal genes. |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_journal-of-molecular-evolution_1995-11_41_5/page/615 |journal=Journal of molecular evolution |date=1995-11 |volume=41 |issue=5 |pages=615-21 |doi=10.1007/BF00175820 |pmid=7490776}}</ref>。他们可能在[[DNA复制|DNA复制]]或通过{{le|基因转换|Gene conversion}}的过程中发生新合成链的{{le|复制滑动|Replication slippage|滑移}}<ref name=Paques/>。

== 序列趋异对系统发生学的解释 ==
ITS序列因為變異不影響核糖體的生成，所以远端物种如人类和青蛙之间进行ITS束序列的比较是不恰当的<ref name=Sumida>{{cite journal |last1=Sumida |first1=M |last2=Kato |first2=Y |last3=Kurabayashi |first3=A |title=Sequencing and analysis of the internal transcribed spacers (ITSs) and coding regions in the EcoR I fragment of the ribosomal DNA of the Japanese pond frog Rana nigromaculata. |journal=Genes & genetic systems |date=2004-04 |volume=79 |issue=2 |pages=105-18 |doi=10.1266/ggs.79.105 |pmid=15215676}}</ref>，但這特性卻很適合在近親之間比較差異。當然反過來說，rDNA编码区域的保守序列则允许远端物种甚至在[[酵母|酵母]]和人类之间进行比较。人类的5.8S rRNA与酵母的5.8S rRNA具有75％的[[同一性|同一性]]<ref name=Nazar>{{cite journal |last1=Nazar |first1=RN |last2=Sitz |first2=TO |last3=Busch |first3=H |title=Sequence homologies in mammalian 5.8S ribosomal RNA. |journal=Biochemistry |date=1976-02-10 |volume=15 |issue=3 |pages=505-8 |doi=10.1021/bi00648a008 |pmid=1252408 |accessdate=2021-09-11}}</ref>。在{{le|姊妹种|Sibling species}}情况下比较包括在物种和[[系统发生学|系统发生学]]中的ITS束则比较顺利<ref name=ma>Ma YJ, Qu FY, Xu JJ. (1998). "Sequence differences of rDNA-ITS2 and species-diagnostic PCR assay of ''Anopheles sinensis'' and ''Anopheles anthropophagus'' from China. ''J Med Coll PLA'' '''13''': 123-128. [http://docs.google.com/viewer?url=http://www.mosquitocatalog.org/files/pdfs/MQ0115.pdf PDF] {{Wayback|url=http://docs.google.com/viewer?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.mosquitocatalog.org%2Ffiles%2Fpdfs%2FMQ0115.pdf |date=20210315143659 }}.</ref><ref name=Li>Li C, Lee JS, Groebner JL, Kim HC, Klein TA, O'Guinn ML, Wilkerson RC (2005). "A newly recognized species in the ''Anopheles'' hyrcanus group and molecular identification of related species from the Republic of South Korea (Diptera: Culicidae)." ''Zootaxa'' '''939''': 1-8. [http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf&AD=ADA505037  PDF] {{Wayback|url=http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf&AD=ADA505037 |date=20130507115708 }}.</ref>。rDNA序列的不同编码区重复序列通常表现出不同的进化速率。其结果是，这种DNA可以提供属于全系统级别的物种的系统发生学信息<ref name=Hillis>{{cite journal |last1=Hillis |first1=DM |last2=Dixon |first2=MT |title=Ribosomal DNA: molecular evolution and phylogenetic inference. |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_quarterly-review-of-biology_1991-12_66_4/page/411 |journal=The Quarterly review of biology |date=1991-12 |volume=66 |issue=4 |pages=411-53 |doi=10.1086/417338 |pmid=1784710 |accessdate=2021-09-11}}</ref>。

